allowance(address,address).details: Function to check the amount of tokens than an owner allowed to a spender.

params._owner: address The address which owns the funds.
params._spender: address The address which will spend the funds.

allowance(address,address).return: A uint specifing the amount of tokens still avaible for the spender.

approve(address,uint256).details: Aprove the passed address to spend the specified amount of tokens on beahlf of msg.sender.

params._spender: The address which will spend the funds.
params._value: The amount of tokens to be spent.

balanceOf(address).details: Gets the balance of the specified address.

params._owner: The address to query the the balance of.

balanceOf(address).return: An uint representing the amount owned by the passed address.

finishMinting().details: Function to stop minting new tokens.
finishMinting().return: True if the operation was successful.

isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

params._amount: The amount of tokens to mint.
params._to: The address that will recieve the minted tokens.

mint(address,uint256).return: A boolean that indicates if the operation was successful.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pause().details: called by the owner to pause, triggers stopped state

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpause().details: called by the owner to unpause, returns to normal state
